
// 🔁 2. Rearrangement / In-place manipulation
//* Rotate the array

//PROBLEM STATEMENT-----


/*


Problem
You are given an integer array nums.
Your task is to rotate the array to the right by k positions, where k is a non-negative integer.
Rotation means shifting elements to the right, and wrapping around the end elements to the front.

Example
Array: 10 20 30 40 50
k = 2
After 1 rotation:
50 10 20 30 40
After 2 rotations:
40 50 10 20 30

Function Declaration
Function Name: rotate
Description:
Rotates the array to the right by k positions in-place.

Parameters
nums → array of integers
k → number of right rotations

Return Value
The function returns nothing
The array must be modified in-place

Constraints
1 ≤ nums.length ≤ 100000
-2³¹ ≤ nums[i] ≤ 2³¹ - 1
0 ≤ k ≤ 100000
Must use O(1) extra space

Input Format
First line contains two integers N and K
Second line contains N space-separated integers

Output Format
Print the rotated array (space-separated).

Sample Input 1
5 2
10 20 30 40 50

Sample Output 1
40 50 10 20 30

Sample Input 2
5 3
7 8 9 1 2

Sample Output 2
9 1 2 7 8

Explanation

Sample 1
After 1 rotation → 50 10 20 30 40
After 2 rotations → 40 50 10 20 30

Sample 2
After 1 rotation → 2 7 8 9 1
After 2 rotations → 1 2 7 8 9
After 3 rotations → 9 1 2 7 8

*/

//SOLUTION---


